      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Music isn’t very present throughout a lot of the game, favoring ambient sounds that accentuate the emptiness of the game world. The machinery throughout has a lot of mechanical foley attached to them, whirring with every turned joint and occasional beeps and digital noise. When music isn’t an ever present part of a game, sound effects become an even more important inclusion. Thankfully, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Retro Machina ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "delivers.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
